jobs_results.title: General Practitioner — Pilot (Men’s Health)
jobs_results.description:
About Pilot

Pilot is an online health platform that makes it easy and safe for Australian men to get access to the prescriptions, products, and medical advice they need for the issues they find hard to talk about. Since launching in 2019, we’ve become one of the fastest-growing telehealth brands in Australia, growing to over 50,000 patients.

Our mission is to enable more men to get help for the conditions that affect their day-to-day lives. We know men are a notoriously hard-to-reach group who are less inclined to talk about their healthcare needs, and we want to help eliminate that hesitancy.

We started out helping men get fast and discreet help for their sexual health needs. We've quickly expanded to other conditions that affect men — hair loss, trouble sleeping, skincare, and obesity.

So how does Pilot work?

We've built a technology platform to deliver healthcare to men with a level of care and depth that brings healthcare into the internet age. We provide an easy-to-use... interface for men to get help, for doctors to manage their consultations via telehealth, and for pharmacies to fulfill any prescriptions, streamlining the user experience from the patient's and doctor's points of view.

This is done by automating the collection of most of the information a doctor needs in a consultation, providing this information in an easy format to doctors so they can make a decision on treatment, and making sure their time is used effectively.

The opportunity

We're currently looking for passionate GPs to join in our goal of making healthcare for men accessible, convenient and safe. Join Pilot in providing men with an online medical support network of qualified specialists like yourself.

Your responsibilities:
• Through telehealth, conduct asynchronous text-based consultations with patients, including assessing, screening, diagnosing, and prescribing medication for patients as necessary
• Adhere to Pilot's platform guidelines and policies and complete all required training
• Provide an exceptional clinical experience for patients through the delivery of prompt and empathetic care on the platform

Essentials:
• Australian Citizen / Australian Permanent Resident / Temporary Resident
• Post-graduate year 4+, with full general or specialist AHPRA registration and full General Registration with the Medical Board of Australia
• Valid medical indemnity insurance
• Skilled at using technology to deliver care and communicate with patients
• Empathetic, friendly, and approachable

Benefits:
• Work from the comfort of your home
• Support from our telehealth customer experience team, medical directors, and GP community
• Payment on a per consult basis
• Use telehealth to provide inclusive, empathetic, and non-stigmatised care and vastly improve the patient experience

jobs_results.title: Director of General Medicine & General Physician
jobs_results.description:
This hospital and health center is seeking a dynamic Clinical Director of General Medicine & General Physician to join our team.

The Location:

Located on the iconic River, this city is one of regional Australia’s most diverse and progressive regional cities, offering a Mediterranean climate and relaxed lifestyle., it boasts the tenth busiest airport in Australia, with direct flights into a number of metropolitan cities. Experience the large variety of restaurants or some of the regions many wineries or take a drive to World Heritage listed National Park – the opportunities are endless.

The region offers great educational opportunities with a selection of private, Catholic and public schools, as well a campus of La Trobe University. This hospital is affiliated with Monash University.

The region is renowned for its big skies, rich earth and welcoming locals. Experience respected wine and bountiful local produce that is served up at quality restaurants and markets, eateries and... cellar doors. Discover breathtaking natural beauty, Mediterranean climate and fascinating local histories.

More than 50,000 people call the region home. The region’s strength lies in its diversity and the range of friendly communities that make up the municipality.

The Hospital:

This is a 165 bed (level 1) Tertiary Teaching Hospital that provides a range of Acute Services including Emergency, Maternity, Intensive Care, General Medicine and Surgery, Medical Imaging, Pathology, Dialysis, Mental Health (Inpatient and community services) and a range of Ambulatory Services. The Hospital is affiliated with Universities for the provision of undergraduate and postgraduate Medical, Nursing and Allied Health education. Affiliations also exist for clinical placement and training.

The Role:

The hospital is looking for an experienced General Physician to lead the Team and Department. It is a fully accredited hospital for RACP training.

You will provide exceptional leadership within a multi-disciplinary team of medical officers and other team members as well as providing supervision and support to doctors in training. Also ensure that care is patient-centred, safe and demonstrates a standard of excellence.

This position will be involved in the training and supervision of medical and nursing staff as required.

Affiliation with two medical universities.

Your Profile:

To be suitable for this role you will need to hold the FRACP have Specialist registration with AHPRA. You must have Australian experience.

For more information please apply or call ALLISHA on 07 3210 633

jobs_results.title: Consultant Emergency Medicine
jobs_results.description:
The Location
Located nearly 600km from state capital, Perth, this town is like nowhere else in Australia. The main street in town is awash with glorious buildings all bearing testament to the wealth that has been generated. It is a city to be savoured with excellent shopping, school, recreational opportunities and a gateway to explore the outback.

The Facility
Our client is a 131-bed hospital with over 350 qualified medical practitioners in what is the regional public hospital in WA. Visitors and locals now have access to upgraded, modern treatment facilities with all clinical works in what has been a $59.6 million redevelopment of the main campus which officially opened in 2015. The completion of clinical works seamlessly ties into earlier phases of the redevelopment which included apalliative care unit, new emergency department, high dependency unit and medical imaging department.

The Position
This role will be to work as a Consultant within an emergency department that is the... main referral hospital for the region and provides patient care to exciting and varied medical challenges. The role is responsible for providing leadership, management, training, supervision and education for Senior Medical Practitioners, Intern, Resident Medical Officers and Registrars in collaboration with the Regional Director of Medical Services.

Requirements
To be suitable for this role you will need to hold the FACEM have Specialist registration with AHPRA. Or be assessed by ACEM and deemed substantially comparable

Pay
Dependant on experience up to $530,000

For more information Apply Now or call Cassidy on 07 3210 6332

jobs_results.title: DPA Vacancy - WA - High remuneration - reduce your moratorium down...
jobs_results.description:
Working as a doctor in the goldfields you can expire your moratorium in 5 years whilst earning $400,000+ and……play golf, chill out by the pool, 4WD, camp, contemplate high art, attend the theatre, go prospecting and hit a seem of gold, shop, relax, explore the Great Australian Bight, dine out and then start all over again....

The Position….

With excellent support from an experienced team of nurses and administrators, you can maximise you time spent with patients at this well managed, modern practice complete with treatment rooms equipped to a high standard and modern and spacious consulting rooms.

Working in a team of 10 GPs, there is ample clinical support with the centre featuring a pathology collection facility, adjacent pharmacy and multi-bed treatment room.

On Offer:
• 70% of all billings.
• Up to $10k relo
• GPRIP Rural incentive payments available
• All doctors participate equally in the roster sharing weekend and public holidays on an equitable basis
• Potential income is... high with some doctors earning over $500,000+
• Half your moratorium

Practice opening hours are:

Monday - Friday: 7:00 am- 8:00 pm

Saturday - Sunday: 8:00 am- 8:00 pm

Public holidays: 8:00 am- 8:00 pm

The practice has a diverse patient base and treats a wide variety of clinical presentations. Services offered by the practice include all aspects of family medicine with doctors who have special interests in the following:
• Children's Health
• Men's Health
• Occupational Health Services
• Travel Medicine
• Women's Health

The Location…..

Kalgoorlie is the hub of the Western Australian Goldfields and the largest city in the Australian Outback. From wild beginnings as a gold rush town full of fortune-seekers it has grown into a bustling cosmopolitan twin city with a distinctive character. And being just an hour’s flight or a day’s drive/train journey from Perth, it’s a popular tourist destination.

The town has a thriving nightlife and a wide variety of modern tourist attractions, shops and leisure facilities. In fact, the city has more restaurants and hotels per capita than any other regional centre in Western Australia, and plays host to many of the region’s biggest events.

Art comes naturally to the many locals who live and work in the community. Photography, painting, drawing and sculpture are showcased at retail outlets, exhibitions and competitions throughout the region.

The Goldfields Arts Centre, located in the centre of town, is the premier entertainment venue in the Goldfields. It has a wide range of state-of-the-art facilities, including a 700-seat theatre, and an A-class gallery, which stages many quality exhibitions throughout the year.
